{"lemma": "صَلِيبٌ", "slug": "صَلِيبٌ", "root": "ص.ل.ب", "root_slug": "ص-ل-ب", "root_link": "/words/roots/ص-ل-ب", "pos": "N", "pos_camel": "noun", "paradigm": [], "frequency_in_corpus": 0, "cross_references": {"qac": {"found": false}, "wiktextract": {"found": true, "entry_count": 4, "pos_tags": ["adj", "noun"], "has_etymology": true, "sense_count": 5}, "lanes": {"found": true, "entry_ids": ["n24683"], "search_url": "https://lanelexicon.com/?s=%D8%B5%D9%8E%D9%84%D9%90%D9%8A%D8%A8%D9%8C"}}, "translations": {"en": "cross", "fa": "صلیب", "ur": "صلیب", "tr": "haç", "id": "salib", "bn": "খ্রিস্টীয় চিহ্ন", "es": "cruz", "fr": "croix", "de": "Kreuz", "ru": "крест", "zh": "十字"}, "definition": {"source": "wiktextract", "senses": [{"pos": "noun", "gloss": "cross (geometrical figure)", "examples": [{"text": "اَلصَّلِيب اَلْجَنُوبِيّ", "english": "Southern Cross"}]}, {"pos": "noun", "gloss": "cross, Cross, crucifix (post for crucifixion)", "tags": ["also"], "examples": [{"text": "لَا تَقُومُ السَّاعَةُ حَتَّى يَنْزِلَ فِيكُمُ ٱبْنُ مَرْيَمَ حَكَمًا مُقْسِطًا، فَيَكْسِرَ الصَّلِيبَ، وَيَقْتُلَ الْخِنْزِيرَ، وَيَضَعَ الْجِزْيَةَ، وَيَفِيضَ الْمَالُ حَتَّى لَا يَقْبَلَهُ أَحَدٌ", "english": "The hour will not arise until the son of Mary comes down upon you as a just ruler, and he will destroy the cross, and he will kill the swine, and abolish the jizya, and fortunes will overflow so that nobody will accept them as gifts."}]}, {"pos": "adj", "gloss": "crucified"}, {"pos": "adj", "gloss": "hard, solid"}, {"pos": "noun", "gloss": "marrow, grease of bones"}]}, "etymology": {"source": "wiktextract", "text": "Etymology tree\nAkkadian 𒁇 (ṣalāpu)bor.\nAramaic צְלִיבָא (ṣəlīḇā)bor.\nArabic صليب\nBorrowed from Aramaic צְלִיבָא (ṣəlīḇā), borrowed from Akkadian 𒁇 (ṣalāpu, “to cross out, to pervert; to give difficulty or be crooked, not be easy or straight”)."}, "ipa": null, "lanes_definition": {"source": "lanes", "entries": [{"entry_id": "n24683", "headword_ar": "صَلِيبٌ", "root": "Slb", "body": [{"kind": "text", "text": ": see"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "SulobN", "text_ar": "صُلْبٌ"}, {"kind": "text", "text": ", former half, in five places. ―         -b2-  [Hence,]"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "maA='N SaliybN", "text_ar": "مَا=ءٌ صَلِيبٌ"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "(tropical:)"}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "Water upon which cattle grow fat and strong and hard."}, {"kind": "text", "text": "(A, TA.) ―         -b3-  And"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "EarabiY~N SaliybN", "text_ar": "عَرَبِىٌّ صَلِيبٌ"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "(tropical:)"}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "An Arabian of pure race:"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "(A, Mgh, TA:) and"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "AimoraA^apN SaliybapN", "text_ar": "اِمْرَاَةٌ صَلِيبَةٌ"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "(tropical:)"}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "A woman of noble,"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "or"}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "generous, origin."}, {"kind": "text", "text": "(A, TA.)       -A2-  Also"}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "Grease,"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "or"}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "oily matter,"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "(S, M, A, Msb, K,) of bones; (S,"}, {"kind": "page_break", "n": 1713}, {"kind": "text", "text": "M, * Msb;) and so ↓"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "SalabN", "text_ar": "صَلَبٌ", "orth_type": "arrow"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "; (M, K;) which latter signifies also"}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "ichor,"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "or"}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "watery humour, mixed with blood, that flows from the dead:"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "(M:) pl. [of the former accord. to analogy, and perhaps of the latter also,]"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "SulubN", "text_ar": "صُلُبٌ"}, {"kind": "text", "text": ". (K.) Hence, in a trad., the phrase"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "A^aSoHaAbu AlS~ulubi", "text_ar": "اَصْحَابُ الصُّلُبِ"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "[in the CK ↓"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "AlS~alabi", "text_ar": "الصَّلَبِ", "orth_type": "arrow"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "]"}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "Those who collect bones,"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "(K, TA,)"}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "when the flesh has been stripped off from them, and cook them with water,"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "(TA,)"}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "and extract their grease,"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "or"}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "oily matter, and use it as a seasoning."}, {"kind": "text", "text": "(K, TA.)       -A3-  Also ["}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "A cross;"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "]"}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "a certain thing pertaining to the Christians,"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "(Lth, S, M, Msb, K,)"}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "which they take as an object to which to direct the face in prayer:"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "(Lth, TA:) pl. [of mult.]"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "SulobaAnN", "text_ar": "صُلْبَانٌ"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "(S, M, A, Msb) and"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "SulubN", "text_ar": "صُلُبٌ"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "(Lth, S, M) and [of pauc.]"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "A^aSolubN", "text_ar": "اَصْلُبٌ"}, {"kind": "text", "text": ". (Msb.) ―         -b2-  [And The"}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "figure of a cross"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "upon a garment &c.: see"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "muSal~abN", "text_ar": "مُصَلَّبٌ"}, {"kind": "text", "text": ".] ―         -b3-  And"}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "A certain brand,"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "or"}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "mark made with a hot iron, upon camels;"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "(M, K;)"}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "which,"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "as Aboo- 'Alee says in the “ Tedhkireh, ”"}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "is sometimes large and sometimes small, and may be upon the cheeks, and the neck, and the thighs:"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "(M, TA:) or, as some say, it is"}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "upon the temple;"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "and as some say,"}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "upon the neck; being two lines, one upon"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "[or"}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "across"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "]"}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "the other."}, {"kind": "text", "text": "(TA.) ―         -b4-  And"}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "i. q."}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "EalamN", "text_ar": "عَلَمٌ"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "[as meaning"}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "A banner,"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "or"}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "standard;"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "properly,"}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "in the form of a cross"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "]: (O, K:) En-Nábighah Edh-Dhubyánee is said to have thus called the"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "Ealam", "text_ar": "عَلَم"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "because there was upon it a"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "Saliyb", "text_ar": "صَلِيب"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "[i. e. a cross]; for he was a Christian. (O.) ―         -b5-  [And hence, as Freytag says, (referring to the “ Historia Halebi ” and “ Locman. Fabul. ” p. ٤٣"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "The text is unclear, the number could be 43 or 42."}, {"kind": "text", "text": "1. 5. 8,) (assumed tropical:)"}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "An army of ten thousand soldiers."}, {"kind": "text", "text": "] ―         -b6-  And"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "AlS~aliybu", "text_ar": "الصَّلِيبُ"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "is the name of"}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "The four stars behind"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "Aln~asoru AlT~aAy^iru", "text_ar": "النَّسْرُ الطَّايِرُ"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "[which is"}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "the asterism consisting of the three principal stars of Aquila;"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "whence it seems to be"}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "the four principal stars of Delphinus"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "]: inconsiderately said by J to be behind"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "Aln~asoru AlwaAqiEu", "text_ar": "النَّسْرُ الوَاقِعُ"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "[which is"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "α", "text_ar": "α", "orth_type": "plain"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "Lyræ]. (L, K, and so in the margin of some copies of the S,) [And Freytag says, (referring to Ideler Unters. p. 35,) that"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "AlSlyb AlwAqE", "text_ar": "الصليب الواقع"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "is the name of (assumed tropical:)"}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "Stars in the head of Draco."}, {"kind": "text", "text": "] ―         -b7-"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "SaliybaAni", "text_ar": "صَلِيبَانِ"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "of a leathern bucket: see 1, last sentence but one.       -A4-  See also"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "maSoluwbN", "text_ar": "مَصْلُوبٌ"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "."}], "source_refs": ["A", "Mgh", "TA", "S", "M", "Msb", "K", "Lth", "O"]}]}, "classical_definitions": null, "translations_attribution": {"model": "qwen36-35b-heretic", "generated_date": "2026-05-14", "pipeline_version": "words.translation.v1.spark"}}